Pulled Chicken Sandwich w/ Red Cabbage Slaw
  --Cook's Country

4 c thinly sliced red cabbage
1/2 c sour cream
2 tbsp bread and butter pickle juice + 1/4 c bread and butter pickles
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp pepper
1 c cider vinegar
1/2 c water
1/4 c sugar
1 tsp red pepper flakes
2 1/2 lb rotisserie chicken, skin and bones discarded, meat shredded into bit sized pieces (3 c)
4 hamburger buns

Combine cabbage, sour cream, pickle juice, 1/2 tsp salt and pepper in bowl; set aside. Bring vinegar, water, sugar, pepper flakes, and remaining salt to boil in medium saucepan over high heat. Cook until reduced by half, 8-10 min. Stir in chicken and cook until warmed through, ~1 min. Remove saucepan from heat. Divide chicken evenly among bun bottoms. Top with 1/2 c slaw, then divide pickles evenly over cabbage. Cover with top buns and serve.


Notes: Can use coleslaw mix in place of red cabbage. 
